![](https://i.imgur.com/x4iIJAq.jpg)

This commemorative stela, located in [Santec](https://goo.gl/maps/4e7ppJfuPiQ2) (France), was raised in honor of the 128 sailors who lost ther life aboard the [HMCS Athabaskan](https://goo.gl/Z6CzRc) in the night of April 19th, 1944.

The Athabaskan was a canadian destroyer which was sunk by the [German torpedo boat T24](https://goo.gl/5ESxwy) during an interception mission in the English Channel, and now lies at 90m depth.

If you are curious about the fate of this ship, you'll find more interesting information [here](https://goo.gl/y6TynL) and [there](https://goo.gl/6P1D1v).

The scan was created from 96 pictures taken with a Canon Eos-1100D, processed with Colmap and OpenMVS, and re-textured and optimized to a lower resolution (~15k triangles) with Blender and [BakeMyScan](http://bakemyscan.org).

Þrívíddarlíkön af Gossvæðinu í Geldingadölum unnin af myndmælingateymi Náttúrufræðistofnunar Íslands. Myndirnar eru teknar úr flugvél og myndmælt í Agisoft Metashape. Verkefnið er unnið í samstarfi við Almannavarnir, Landmælingar Íslands og Háskóla Ísland.


3D models of the eruption site at Geldingadalir created by the photogrammetry department of the Icelandic Institute of Natural History. The photographs are taken from an aircraft and processed in Agisoft Metashape. The models are developed in collaboration with the Civil Protection and Emergency Management of Iceland, The National Land Survey of Iceland and the University of Iceland.

revolt on territory forming modern-day Croatia and Slovenia. The revolt, sparked by cruel treatment of serfs by Baron Ferenc Tahy, who resided in the fortress of Susedgrad, ended after 12 days with the defeat of the rebels and bloody retribution by the nobility. In the late 16th century, the threat of Ottoman incursions strained the economy of the southern flanks of the Holy Roman Empire, and feudal lords continually increased their demands on the peasantry. In Croatian Zagorje, this was compounded by cruel treatment of peasants by baron Ferenc Tahy and his disputes with neighbouring barons over land, dating back to 1564, which escalated into armed conflicts. Battle of Stubica was fought. ![borgstugan](https://pub.raa.se/nedladdning/sketchfab/bilder/lokaliseringssymboler/Bstuga.jpg?dl=0&raw=1)

Nu är du i en sal som heter Borgstugan.
Jens hade många besökare som han tog emot här. Rummet användes även som tillhåll och matsal för borgens soldater och en del tjänstefolk. Ibland hölls gårdsrätt här. Det var som en slags domstol på medeltiden där man kunde reda ut allt möjligt. Alltid var det någon som hade tagit kockens slev, druckit av ölet innan det var färdigjäst eller släppt in byrackorna i borgstugan. Där tycker jag det var bra att någon satte ned tassen!
Så här kunde det se ut på ett ungefär när Jens styrde och ställde härinne.
![vderweyden](https://pub.raa.se/nedladdning/sketchfab/bilder/van_der_Weyden.jpg?dl=0&raw=1)Målning av R van der Weyden,1447 [Upphovsrätt bild: Public Domain](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Van_der_weyden_miniature.jpg)

'https://api.sketchfab.com/v3/users/460d22e3fb12415fbd5e423282b8655a'}, 'description': 'A obra militar nº 10, «Forte da Carvalha», fez parte da 1º Linha de defesa do Distrito nº 1 das chamadas "Linhas de Torres Vedras", cuja construção teve o seu início no ano de 1809, durante a segunda invasão peninsular das tropas francesas lideradas pelo Marechal Soult. Pela mesma altura, o duque de Wellington decide defender Lisboa, mandando edificar aquele que é considerado o mais eficiente sistema de fortificações de campo da História militar.
O Forte da Carvalha foi construido a 394m de altitude, tendo detido uma guarnição de 400 homens, que serviam uma estrutura com 4 canhoeiras: 2 peças de calibre 12 e 2 peça de calibre 9.
Fazia fogo cruzado com o Forte do Cego, constituindo os principais redutos defensivos do vale de Arruda.
